1. Definitions.

"License" shall mean the terms and conditions for use, reproduction,
and distribution as defined by Sections 1 through 9 of this document.

"Licensor" shall mean the copyright owner or entity authorized by
the copyright owner that is granting the License.

"Medical Standards Data" shall mean the ICD-10, SNOMED CT, LOINC,
RxNorm, FHIR, and clinical guidelines content contained in the data/
directory, each subject to their respective organization licenses
(IHTSDO, WHO, Regenstrief, HL7).

2. Medical Standards Data License.

The Medical Standards Data (data/ directory) includes codes,
terminology, and references from:
- ICD-10: World Health Organization (WHO)
- SNOMED CT: IHTSDO (International Health Terminology Standards
  Development Organisation)
- LOINC: Regenstrief Institute, Inc.
- RxNorm: National Library of Medicine (NLM)
- FHIR: Health Level Seven International (HL7)
- Clinical Guidelines: Respective medical organizations (ADA, AHA,
  WHO, etc.)

Each standard's data is subject to its respective license agreement.
This repository aggregates public reference data for interoperability
purposes only.

